com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.receivers

Class ReceiversRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.RequestExecutor<T>
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.PaginatedRequestExecutor<Receivers>
        • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.receivers.ReceiversRequestExecutor

  • public class ReceiversRequestExecutor
extends PaginatedRequestExecutor<Receivers>
    Request executor provided by ReceiversApi. Use this class if you want to obtain receivers through fluent API in chained fashion, for instance: 
       
   KontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloudFactory.create();
   Receivers receivers = kontaktCloud.receivers().fetch()
      .fromPlaces(placeIDs)
      .maxResult(10)
      .execute();
